cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it proposes a new encoding method for language models. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the use of neural networks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the development of a new method for encoding variable-length sequences. It could also be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the use of feedforward neural networks. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as FOFE has been applied to image classification tasks in previous works.
